FBIS3-25201 "drafr028_c_94011" FBIS-AFR-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA UK's Hurd Cancels 4-Day Official Visit to Region MB0902160194 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1400 GMT 9 Feb 94 MB0902160194 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd has canceled a four-day trip to South Africa and Swaziland because of events in Bosnia. This has been announced in London by British officials, who said that Mr. Hurd had not yet rearranged his trip to southern Africa. However, they said it would not take place in the immediate future. Mr. Hurd was to have left today for the visit that included meetings with State President F.W. de Klerk and ANC [African National Congress] leader Mr. Nelson Mandela.
